frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=895.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Progressions</span><hr size=1> Part of the problem with the smaller guilds or family guilds as they've been termed etc.. well let me restate that somewhat, part of the problem I've seen has been the way the smaller guilds are made up. This is more a problem for the leadership than anything.<br>
<br>
I've been in 2 guilds in my entire EQ career. I joined JD primarily a family/fun loving guild rather early on in my EQ playtime. JD was a great guild and had lots of potential but the ppl that &quot;raided&quot; and organized the high lvl events were basically shunned by the other officers. Yeah, basically 4 of the many officers in JD were raiding and trying to get the guild moving on various things. We were wanting to make the high lvl game more entertaining and fun by being able to do things. Part of the problem I think we encountered was our playstyles were more apt for the high lvl game(the 4 of us that were raiding and organizing things). What this did was shift the focus away from the longtime leaders who had been more about RP and other things than raiding for the first 50 or so lvls.<br>
<br>
The biggest problem with this was the transition. Very seldom are the leaders of the smaller guilds the individuals who operate and run the raids for higher lvls cause seldom do these smaller guilds start out with the intent to raid in mind. They just got together as a group of friends who wanted to spend time together and chat etc. IMO the biggest downfall in JD was the fact that the original Leaders of the guild didn't like the shift in power at the high lvl game due to the nature of the high lvl game changing to that of a more raid atmosphere. Eventually this broke alot of JD apart which is now in the past.<br>
<br>
The 4 Officers who tried to move JD into the Higher lvl game of raids and big mobs broke off and eventually formed DV. Well, DV is doing just fine as a raid guild and being able to approach the guild from a ground lvl buildup(well, we started in the low 50's) has allowed us to build the guild in such a way that we have few of the problems alot of other guilds have. We don't have mass amounts of players who dislike each other cause of different goals. Sure sometimes we run into differences of opinion but we solve them in mature fashion. And the good news is DV's retention past the trial period is one of the best on the server.<br>
<br>
What I find humorous about the initial post is listing 2 guilds for high success and longevity. That, is so unrealistic it's laughable. And you mean to tell me Quad won't be around further down the line? Build your guild with the right goals in mind, stay away from problem ppl or ppl who can't find a home and you'll do just fine. What you have to realize when joining one of the high lvl guilds on the server is that the high lvl game is an investment. If you can't invest, spare everyone the trouble and don't apply.<br>
<br>
<br>
Cin <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showPrevMessage?topicID=895.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showNextMessage?topicID=895.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=895.topic&index=12><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/march/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.emailToFriend?topicID=895.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.threadControl?topicID=895.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=895.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=895.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub18.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsfrm41">Everquest Daily News<option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40">EverQuest Rants-n-Flames<option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsfrm23">Raid Intentions<option value="mithanielmarrdailynewsf